# TOKEN EFFICIENCY

- No yapping: do not add greetings, summaries, or closing remarks.
- Default to code-first replies: show the patch or function before any explanation.
- Show only the changed code or the minimal surrounding context needed to understand it.
- Do NOT reprint entire files unless explicitly requested.
- When multiple options exist, list them briefly, then implement the recommended one only.
- Keep natural-language explanations under 5 short sentences unless I ask for a deep dive.
- When a change touches many files, summarize the change set and only expand files or hunks I ask about.
